node.text:
.
When starting Bodies by Rachel I had one clear goal, to help educate and transform as many women's lives as possible. I wanted to show women how much fitness could change their lives, the way it did mine. Since then, BBR has grown into something so much bigger than I could have ever dreamed or imagined. Today, it's time to close one chapter, and say hello to a brand new future.

This is so much more than a name change. This is our first step in a new direction - a direction that I promise will provide you with more than you've ever imagined. 

✨New Coaches (announced soon)
✨New Challenges
✨Live Workouts (choose your coach and training style)
✨Browse Multiple Meal Guides (a nutrition experience like never before!)
✨Brand New Recipes 
✨Hundreds of New Workouts in our Workout Library 
✨Move your Mindset With @alexispredez
✨Favourite Recipes, Workouts & Videos

Updates to everything you know and love➕ we have a lot more on the way😻

None of this is possible without you, and every moment of love, sweat and tears that the Team and I have put into this has been done for you. This business has always been about one thing, our clients, and that will never, ever change. 

I have so much more to explain, and promise that I will answer ALL of your questions over the coming days so stay tuned on my Story for updates! 

LET'S MOVE❤️

.
Hiiiiii❤️

I’m currently eating 6x days in a mild deficit & 1x high day!

I decided to choose 4x meals from the @bodiesbyrachel App that I have not yet tried and well WOW🤤

The KEY to long term results are
✨Flexibility. 
Flexibility has allowed me to have so much control over what I eat. I failed at flexible dieting multiple times before I succeeded. It took me a long time to shift my mindset from ‘good’ and ‘bad’ food to just food/energy. 

This week we challenged our BBR girls to step outside their Meal Guides and use the BBR Food journal & Recipes to be flexible! It’s been amazing to watch so many of them over time transition into flexible dieting. 

✨Pre-Planning.
Being flexible still requires planning. I don’t think it matters how advanced you are. Planning is the key to success, but remember things don’t always go to plan, and we have to learn that it’s okay and we just do our beet to work around it. 

✨Consistency.
I don’t know how many times you’ve all heard me say this but consistency trumps perfection ANYDAY! Focus on all the small changes you are making because I promise you they add up. Mistakes are okay, they are great imo. Because we learn and we improve. We often learn more in our losses then we do in our success. 

✨ Education.
Keep learning, be eager to know more, experiment with new things. Having an understanding of why and how to do things correctly allows for more flexibility. 
-No protein shake, great I can have an egg white omelette instead.
-No laying hamstring curl machine, great I can use a dumbbell instead. 
The more we know, the easier this becomes.

Be patient, keep working, keep improving.
Whatever you do, don’t let your own journey overwhelm you, your inspos started somewhere too, remember that❤️

Let me know if you want to see a high day?

node.text:
.
.
One of my fave post workout meals!

So quick and easy, prepare yourself... these are delicious! 
.
Calories: 240.3
P: 20.7g  C: 28.8g  F: 4.7g⁣
⁣
✨ Ingredients:⁣
➡️ 1 wholemeal English Muffin⁣
➡️ 100g Egg Whites ⁣
➡️ 30g Turkey Breast Slices ⁣
➡️ 15g Vegan Mozzarella ⁣
➡️ Salt and Pepper, to taste ⁣⁣
⁣
✨ Optional Additions:⁣
➡️ Sugar Free BBQ or Tomato Sauce ⁣
⁣
✨ Method:⁣
1️⃣Spray a bowl with cooking spray. Pour egg whites into the bowl and place in a microwave for 90 seconds. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. 
⁣
2️⃣Lightly spray a pan on medium heat with coconut oil. When hot, add turkey slices and let them develop a slightly brown crust. Then add cheese and leave for an extra 30 seconds or until melted slightly. 
⁣
3️⃣Toast the english muffin while waiting. 
⁣
4️⃣Add the egg whites and turkey slices to the english muffin and top with a sauce of your choice! 
⁣
Enjoy!😍

WEEKEND PANCAKES ANYONE? This recipe is 🤤
.
Calories: 442.5⁣
P: 38.7g | C: 47.4g | F: 10.6g⁣
⁣
✨ Ingredients:⁣
➡️ 30g of Vanilla Protein Powder⁣
➡️ 25g of Blueberries⁣
➡️ Zest and Juice from 1/2 Lemon⁣
➡️ 8g of Honey⁣
➡️ 1 tsp of Vanilla Extract⁣
➡️ 60g of Rolled Oats⁣
➡️ 1 Egg(s)⁣
➡️ 1/4 tsp of Baking Soda⁣
➡️ 1 tbsp of Plant Based Milk⁣
⁣
✨ Optional Additions:⁣
➡️ Sugar Free Maple Syrup⁣
⁣
✨ Method:⁣
1️⃣ In a blender, combine protein, lemon juice, honey, vanilla extract, oats, egg, baking soda, and plant based milk. Blend until smooth. After blending, stir in blueberries and lemon zest.⁣
⁣
2️⃣ Lightly spray a pan on medium heat with coconut oil. When hot, pour enough pancake batter onto pan to create the desired size pancakes you'd like.⁣
⁣
3️⃣ When the pancake starts slightly bubbling at the surface, flip it to the other side and cook for another 1-2 minutes.⁣
⁣
4️⃣ Serve hot with sugar free maple syrup!⁣
⁣
💡Recipe hack: ⁣
➖ Prep and store your pancake batter in the freezer⁣
➖ Large silicone ice cube trays make for a great serving size⁣
➖ Let the batter defrost in silicone mold for 10-15 mins first⁣
➖ Cook on a low heat ⁣
⁣
Enjoy!😍

node.text:
Hi🙋🏽‍♀️

Here to remind you that you are not what you do sometimes but what you do consistently. Stop stressing over that meal you overindulged in or the workout you missed. 

People get health and fitness all wrong because they think it has to rule your life when really it should compliment it. Life is to be enjoyed, don’t sweat the small stuff.

Find a style of training you love, eat to feel good and show up consistently. I promise you, you will create a lifestyle you love and can adhere to! 

Here’s a little fun Quad Giant Set for you😜
1. 10x Dumbbell Sissy Squats 
2. 10x Dumbbell Split Squats E/L
3. 10x Dumbbell Box Squats
4. 10x Dumbbell Box Squat Jumps 
5 Sets 

✖️Minimal rest between each exercise!
✖️90 seconds rest between sets. 
Note: I used a set of 15kg Dumbbells. 

@movewithus

node.text:
GLUTES & QUADS🔥

It’s been a while since I’ve shared a lower body workout, which is very rude and unlike me👀

A little taste of Bikini Build 3.0🥵 

1. Barbell Squats
Warm-up sets: 1 x 10, 1 x 8
Work sets: 8 (60kg), 6 (70kg), 4 (80kg), 4 (80kg), 6 (70kg), 8 (60kg)
Tempo: 4110
Rest between sets: 2 minutes
 
1. Barbell Walking Lunges
Work sets: 3 x 8
 
2. Cable Kickbacks
Work sets: 3 x 12
Rest between sets: 90 seconds 

1. Dumbbell Hip Thrusts 
Work sets: 3x 20

2. Side Step Ups 
Work sets: 3x 10 (each leg)
Rest between triple sets: 60 seconds

New challenge coming soon👀
@movewithus

node.text:
SPICY AB FINISHER🔥

Add this ab finisher to the end of your next workout🥵

Equipment
✖️Set of Dumbbells
✖️Set of Ankle Weights

Can also complete this without equipment! No excuses😏, let’s go @movewithus 

1. 20x Reverse Crunches 
2. 10x Oblique Sit Ups (each side) 
3.  20x Sit Ups 
4. 20x Leg Raise Complex 
5. 20x Bird Dogs 
6. 20x Plank Rocks 
2-3 Sets 

Enjoy✌🏼 @movewithus

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Rachel Dillon💫 on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
Photo shared by Rachel Dillon💫 on September 12, 2021 tagging @emmajane.dillon. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
The morning we found out @emmajane.dillon & @adamduffy got some exciting news post their first round of IVF (I’ll let her share-*not preg this was taken weeks ago*). 

So proud of my sister for being so vulnerable and sharing her journey. It really is sad how little this topic is spoken about. Growing up as a girl and even to this day I was very uneducated around fertility. I believed you grew up, met someone and conceived, but it really is not that simple for so many. 

Excited to support and learn through this journey with my sister and my bestfriend🤍

Second to this a gentle piece of advice. Be careful the pressure you unintentionally put on females/relationships around having children, as I said it really isn’t so simple for everyone, so be kind and compassionate. 

Exciting times ahead and I can’t wait to be an Aunty to my nephew.. yes I’m calling it, I have a feeling it’s a going to be a boy-however we just want a healthy baby and we will be so happy-lol me speaking like the baby is mine…because it pretty much will have two mums because Emma and I are one🙃

Manifesting is in full force (I even talk to her follicles🙋🏽‍♀️) haha love you both so much✨

PS. My mum was crying and we made her get a photo😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Rachel Dillon💫 on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
Photo shared by Rachel Dillon💫 on September 09, 2021 tagging @photosbyjt, @simmycarr, and @movewithus. May be an image of 1 person and ocean.

node.text:
Swipe for message🤍

I know this is a physical transformation and that’s what you can see and judge, but these two photos go so much deeper than that.

The girl on the left spent her days googling how to eat and exercise like the models she would see in magazines. She would idolise body types that simply were not genetically possible for her. She was in a vicious cycle of under-eating and overtraining, wondering why her body wasn’t changing. She wasn’t educated. She wasn’t confident. She wasn’t happy. 

So, what changed? I knew what wasn’t working for me, and made a promise to figure out what would. I studied, got qualified, and began trialling different approaches until I found a style of training and way of eating that I actually enjoyed. 

I then began to train big groups of amazing women. I thought to myself how can I inspire these girls to love themselves if I can’t do the same? At that moment I decided to wholeheartedly accept me for me, choosing to enjoy who I was and where I was in my fitness journey whilst working on creating my best possible self. 

The girl on the right embraces herself, is resilient and strong. Again not just strong physically but most importantly mentally too! 

We often look to fitness as a way to change the way we look, when it’s really all about changing the way we feel. Progress occurs in many different ways, learn to recognise it in all forms.

PS. In no way am I saying my body on the left was bad, I think I look great. However that’s not what’s important in this message. 

Love watching my @movewithus community grow every single day✨

node.text:
How to indulge on your holiday but still stay on track? 

The last thing you want to do whilst on holidays is worry about taking too many steps backwards. So don’t stress, enjoy every single moment. 

A few tips that I do when travelling🌴

1. I fast until about 10 or 11am. I know I’ll be eating out most nights so I find pushing my meals back a little helps with saving more of my calories for later in the day. 
2. I start my day with 1L of water, a coffee and either go for a light walk or do a mini workout. Moving first thing gets it out of the way and allows me to relax for the rest of the day.
3. Walk more. I know I’ll be consuming more calories on holiday, so if I can increase my movement that’s going to help me balance out my energy expenditure. 
4. Do a grocery shop. I personally plan for 1-2 meals out and 1-2 meals in. Again this helps with having some control. 
5. Give and take! If you want to have a few cocktails, maybe skip your entree or dessert. If you want to have dessert maybe skip your drinks! A little compromise each day goes a long way. 

OR, don’t do any of the above and enjoy your holiday your way! The purpose of a holiday is pleasure, so structure your days in a way that you’ll enjoy. Don’t feel guilty, and don’t get home and take extreme measures to compensate.

Education allows for flexibility & freedom!
 
@movewithus

CARAMEL LATTE OR STRAWBERRY MATCHA?

Iced Caramel Latte☕️
✖️1/2 cup ice
✖️1 shot coffee
✖️10g caramel sauce
✖️250mls almond milk 

Iced Strawberry Matcha Latte🍓
✖️4 Strawberries (diced)
✖️2 sweeteners 
Mash up! 
✖️1/2 cup ice
✖️250mls almond milk 
✖️2tsp matcha

Both approx 100 calories! 

Enjoy🤍

Recipes inspire by @7amcoffeeclub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Rachel Dillon💫 on September 03, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '16 MINUTE AB CIRCUIT'.

node.text:
16MIN AB CIRCUIT🔥

Happy weekend, another day in paradise for me👙🌴 

Quick little ab session to start my morning and get moving🔥

1.  30sec Reverse Crunch Complex
2. 30sec Toe Taps
3. 30sec Single Leg Raises 
4. 30sec Oblique Reaches
5. 30sec Bicycles 
6. 30sec Plank
7. 30sec Shoulder Taps
8. 30sec Moving Plank 
4 Rounds

Love using the @movewithus library for quick on the go workouts! You can trial workouts from any of our coaches❤️‍🔥

LEGS + A LITTLE CORE🔥

Another holiday workout coming your way! For those with minimal equipment, this one is for you🥵

Equipment
✖️Set of Dumbbells
✖️Booty Band (optional-can do without)

1. 10x OH DB Squats
2. 10x DB Jump Squats 
3 Sets

1. 20x DB RDLs
2. 20x DB Walking Single Leg RDLs 
4 Sets

1. 20x Dumbbell Squats
2. 20x Dumbbell Walking Lunges (up hill)
4 Sets

Finisher
1. 20x Banded Side Steps 
2. 20x Banded Jumping Lunges
3. 10x Burpees
4. 20x Leg Raises 
2 Sets 

Train anywhere and anytime with @movewithus 

Enjoy x
